<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,302,705]" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">
Endemic to the Atlantic Forest (
<bibRefCitation author="Sobral, M. &amp; Lucas, E. &amp; Landrum, L. &amp; Soares-Silva, L." box="[526,737,341,367]" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" pagination="352 - 366" refId="ref15003" refString="Sobral, M., Lucas, E., Landrum, L. &amp; Soares-Silva, L. (2009) Myrtaceae. In: Stehmann, J., Forzza, R. C., Salino, A., Sobral, M., Costa, D. P. &amp; Kamino, L. H. Y. Plantas da Floresta Atlantica. Rio de Janeiro, pp 352 - 366." type="book chapter" year="2009">
Sobral 
<emphasis box="[612,670,341,366]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">et al.</emphasis>
2009
</bibRefCitation>
) from the northeast to nouthern regions of 
<collectingCountry box="[1242,1313,341,367]" name="Brazil" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sobral, M. &amp; Proenca, C. &amp; Souza, M. &amp; Mazine, F. &amp; Lucas, E." pageId="10" pageNumber="43" refId="ref15080" refString="Sobral, M., Proenca, C., Souza, M., Mazine, F. &amp; Lucas, E. (2010) Myrtaceae. In: Forzza, R. C., Leitman, P. M., Costa, A. F., Carvalho Jr., A. A., Peixoto, A. L., Walter, B. M. T., Bicudo, C., Zappi, D., Costa, D. P., Lleras, E., Martinelli, G., Lima, H. C., Prado, J., Stehmann, J. R., Baumgratz, J. F. A., Pirani, J. R., Sylvestre, L., Maia, L. C., Lohmann, L. G., Queiroz, L. P., Silveira, M., Coelho, M. N., Mamede, M. C., Bastos, M. N. C., Morim, M. P., Barbosa, M. R., Menezes, M., Hopkins, M., Secco, R., Cavalcanti, T. B. &amp; Souza, V. C. Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro. Published on the internet; http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / 2010 / FB 010791. Accessed: 5 October 2011." type="url" year="2010">
Sobral 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
). In the northeast, it is recorded from the States of 
<collectingRegion box="[869,939,378,404]" country="Brazil" name="Bahia" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Bahia</collectingRegion>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Sobral, M. &amp; Proenca, C. &amp; Souza, M. &amp; Mazine, F. &amp; Lucas, E." box="[956,1178,378,404]" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" refId="ref15080" refString="Sobral, M., Proenca, C., Souza, M., Mazine, F. &amp; Lucas, E. (2010) Myrtaceae. In: Forzza, R. C., Leitman, P. M., Costa, A. F., Carvalho Jr., A. A., Peixoto, A. L., Walter, B. M. T., Bicudo, C., Zappi, D., Costa, D. P., Lleras, E., Martinelli, G., Lima, H. C., Prado, J., Stehmann, J. R., Baumgratz, J. F. A., Pirani, J. R., Sylvestre, L., Maia, L. C., Lohmann, L. G., Queiroz, L. P., Silveira, M., Coelho, M. N., Mamede, M. C., Bastos, M. N. C., Morim, M. P., Barbosa, M. R., Menezes, M., Hopkins, M., Secco, R., Cavalcanti, T. B. &amp; Souza, V. C. Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro, Rio de Janeiro. Published on the internet; http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / 2010 / FB 010791. Accessed: 5 October 2011." type="url" year="2010">
Sobral 
<emphasis box="[1044,1105,378,403]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
). New records of this species for State of 
<collectingRegion box="[381,530,416,442]" country="Brazil" name="Pernambuco" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Pernambuco</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[542,638,416,442]" country="Brazil" name="Alagoas" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Alagoas</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion box="[695,784,416,442]" country="Brazil" name="Sergipe" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Sergipe</collectingRegion>
are presented here.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[151,1436,302,705]" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">
Trees 
<quantity box="[270,336,453,479]" metricMagnitude="0" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="6.0" metricValueMin="4.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" unit="m" value="5.0" valueMax="6.0" valueMin="4.0">4–6m</quantity>
tall. This species differs from 
<taxonomicName box="[695,940,454,479]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Marlierea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="tomentosa">
<emphasis box="[695,940,454,479]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Marlierea tomentosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in having smaller leaves (7–12 × 
<quantity box="[1339,1427,453,479]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" metricValueMax="5.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" unit="cm" value="4.0" valueMax="5.0" valueMin="3.0">3–5 cm</quantity>
) and glabrous fruit; it differs from other 
<taxonomicName box="[611,785,491,517]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Myrtaceae" genus="Myrcia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Myrtales" pageId="10" pageNumber="43" phylum="Magnoliopsida" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis box="[611,694,491,516]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="43">Myrcia</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
by the calyx closed in the bud, tearing open irregularly.
</paragraph>
